2. In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires- Interpretation
"aggrieved party" means any person whose application for registration under Part II
has been refused or made subject to any condition by the Certifying
Authority, or any person who had been registered under Part II and whose
registration has been cancelled by the Certifying Authority;
"authorised officer" means an officer appointed under section three.
"certified seed" means any prescribed seed which is certified under the provisions
of Part VIII;
"contract of sale" includes an agreement to sell;
"Certifying Agency" means any seed company or institution licenced as a seed
testing station under Part II.
"Certifying Authority" means the person designated as such in pursuance of the
provisions of section three;
